The paper deals with distributed algorithms and rational agents, which are topics commonly studied in game theory (cs.GT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The focus on the amount of global information required for equilibrium suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of algorithms and equilibria also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
